---
// src/pages/docs/vue/install.astro
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Install & Overview - Vue">
  <div
    class="mb-4 text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest"
  >
    @elekcsv/vue
  </div>

  <h1 class="mb-8 border-b-2 border-black pb-4">3.1 Install & Overview</h1>

  <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    The <code>@elekcsv/vue</code> package provides a highly optimized <code
      >useCSVImporter</code
    > composable. It wraps the headless <code>@elekcsv/core</code> engine, bringing
    zero-allocation parsing directly into your Vue 3 reactivity system.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    The package is designed to be UI-agnostic. We give you the state machine and
    the parsing engine; you render the buttons and the dropzones.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npm install @elekcsv/vue @elekcsv/core
# or
yarn add @elekcsv/vue @elekcsv/core
# or
pnpm add @elekcsv/vue @elekcsv/core</code></pre>

  <h2>Why the Vue Composable?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">No Main Thread Blocking:</strong> Large CSV files
      are parsed asynchronously using web workers (or time-sliced chunks) under the
      hood to ensure your Vue UI never freezes.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Reactive State Machine:</strong> The composable
      instantly provides reactive Refs like <code>isLoading</code>, <code
        >isComplete</code
      >, and <code>hasErrors</code> without you needing to manage custom <code
        >ref</code
      > jungles.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Bring Your Own UI:</strong> Unlike other libraries
      that force ugly, unstylable iframes or modals, `elekcsv` gives you raw data.
      Render it with Tailwind, Vuetify, or plain CSS.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-16 flex justify-end">
    <a
      href="/docs/vue/basic"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-neutral-800 no-underline! transition-colors"
      style="text-decoration:none;"
    >
      Next: Basic Usage
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        ><path
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
